Marius Fransman (File, Sapa) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Cape Town&rsquo;s most notorious gangster Mark Lifman was a VIP guest at President Jacob Zuma&rsquo;s recent birthday rally at the Vygieskraal Stadium in Athlone.According to the Sunday Times, Lifman &ndash; who was photographed with ANC provincial chairperson Marius Fransman &ndash; has been under investigation by various agencies for numerous crime-related issues.A senior ANC leader in Cape Town said that Fransman&rsquo;s association with the gangster could do serious damage to the party&rsquo;s election campaign image. The ANC leader said that Lifman was notorious for his involvement in crime and questioned how he could be a VIP guest of the president.Another ANC leader in the province slammed Fransman&rsquo;s relationship with known gangsters. He said it was well known that Lifman gave the ANC money ahead of elections. &ldquo;Why else would he be allowed so close to the president,&rdquo; asked the ANC leader. Fransman under spotlightFransman came under the spotlight earlier this month when he walked out of a Scopa hearing. Along with the Western Cape&rsquo;s former health MEC Pierre Uys, the two were summoned to appear before Scopa to be questioned on the Auditor General&rsquo;s report on the use of consultants. The report showed irregularities and mismanagement of public funds."They chose to walk out. It makes a mockery of the processes and acts of Parliament," Scopa chairperson Grant Haskin told Sapa. NEW! Explore previous National and Provincial election results with our interactive Results Maps by clicking here. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.